cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with natural language inference (NLI) and the analysis of models' ability to understand both lexical and compositional semantics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning models and their performance evaluation, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the architecture of models, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses natural language examples, which could potentially relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) if the examples involve visual information.
